   "body" : "WIP draft of a minimum viable `netaddress` patch to remove tor v2 support, which has been removed from the upcoming release of tor 0.4.6.\r\n\r\n- No longer serialize and relay tor v2 addresses\r\n- Ignore incoming tor v2 addresses\r\n- Auto-remove tor v2 addresses from addrman and peers.dat\r\n\r\nTested with tor-0.4.6.1-alpha. Removes warnings like those reported in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/21351\r\n\r\n```\r\nbitcoind debug log\r\nSocks5() connect to [â¦].onion:8333 failed: general failure\r\n\r\ntor log\r\nInvalid hostname [scrubbed]; rejecting\r\n```\r\n\r\nand the addrman no longer has tor v2 addresses on launching bitcoind:\r\n```rake\r\n$ ./src/bitcoin-cli -addrinfo\r\n{\r\n  \"addresses_known\": {\r\n    \"ipv4\": 43470,\r\n    \"ipv6\": 8263,\r\n    \"torv2\": 0,\r\n    \"torv3\": 2122,\r\n    \"i2p\": 6,\r\n    \"total\": 53861\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
